        <scopecontent id="ref5">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>Manuscript and photocopied material of Lucy S. Freeland of Miwok myths told by Thomas Williams and Lena Cox. Off prints from the Hudson Review of myth translations by Jaime de Angulo. Also, working documents of Howard Berman for the published work Freeland’s Central Sierra Miwok Myths, 1982.</p>
            <p>Native American Images note : Primarily images of coyote, the Miwok creator god, the black and white illustrations accompany the text of “Seven Indian Tales” by Jaime de Angulo. Originally printed in the Hudson Review, an offprint of the published work Indian Tales (1952).</p>
